Package: BayesLinReg
Title: Bayesian Linear Regression with Flexible Coefficient Priors
Version: 10.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(
        "Fabio", "Morgante",
        email = "fabiom@clemson.edu",
        role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Fits Bayesian linear regression models from raw observations or
    sufficient statistics with one or more predictor blocks. Coefficients can
    be assigned independent normal, spike-and-slab, BayesR-style
    spike-and-multiple-slab, or beta-prime global-local priors, including
    Strawderman-Berger and
    horseshoe specifications. Supports known or inverse-gamma-modeled residual
    variance, sampled coefficient-prior variances, Gibbs sampling implemented
    in R or 'Rcpp', optional parallel chains, memory-efficient online
    posterior summaries, predictor standardization, and convergence
    diagnostics.
